EmailTemplate.name: Severe Issue - Burning Charger (Missing contact)
EmailTemplate.subject: Burning Chargers
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
WARNING - ERROR
Hello, Please manually send the following email and ensure that merchant got at least one quality or business contact with an email address. Make sure to always put legal-sellers@backmarket.com in cc of your email.
--
Dear Merchant,
Several buyers have drawn our attention to a potentially very alarming situation concerning smartphone or laptop power chargers that have been provided through our platform. According to these buyers their charger has overheated or burned, posing a serious threat to their safety. You can refer to the following order IDs: {!Alert__c.Order_IDs__c}.
Any seller active on our platform must ensure that the chargers he delivers comply with the international Safety Standard IEC 62368-1. In order to assess this compliance, we are requiring you to send your Back Market point of contact the following information about all chargers you are currently distributing:
If you are providing original/refurbished chargers: the documentation of your unitary control process
If you are providing chargers sourced from manufacturers:
the following 4-5 pictures of the specified charger [jpeg format required, size <5MB]
1. All sides with some marking - marking must be readable
2. One side of the charger - If not displayed in 1
3. Top side with the DC plug
4. Populated PCB (top side)
5. Populated PCB (bottom side)
The charger model should correspond to the one of the concerned order ID.
the full test report LVD for that charger model: the test report LVD should be in accordance with the standard IEC 62368-1 (the new mandatory standard since Dec 2020)
Please find in Appendix and attached examples of what will be considered adequate information.
Please note that we can support you to secure high quality sourcing thanks to our component offer that includes charging blocks/chargers certified by international standards (IEC 62368-1). If you are interested, feel free to reach out to your usual point of contact for more information.
Considering the seriousness of the situation, we rely on your cooperation and ask you to provide us with the above documentation within 30 days.
The failure to do so could lead us to consider that you are in breach of articles 8, 12, 13, 14 of our T&Cs on requirements relating to risks and legal guarantee of conformity. In such a case, Back Market is considering taking all appropriate measures, including sales restriction, suspension and closing of your account.
We also remind you that, as a seller, you are accountable for customer's safety regarding the use of products or accessories you deliver and therefore responsible for checking their composition upon batch reception. Also, you shall take all actions to correct the situation (e.g. recall of products, reimbursement, formal warning to clients etc).
Your Back Market point of contact is available to explain the situation further and provide you with support to handle the situation. Please consider this email as a formal notice to communicate some information with all legal consequences attached.
Have a nice day,
THE BACK MARKET TEAM
